details:
Case 116 is a 50 year-old female Singapore Citizen who has no recent travel history to affected countries and regions. She is currently warded in an isolation room at NCID. She is linked to the cluster involving a private dinner function at SAFRA Jurong.

She reported onset of symptoms on 29 February and had sought treatment at a GP clinic on 1 March and 3 March. As she had attended the private dinner function at SAFRA Jurong on 15 February, she was referred by MOH to National Centre for Infectious Diseases (NCID), and was immediately isolated. Subsequent test results confirmed COVID-19 infection on 5 March morning.

Prior to hospital admission, she had mostly stayed at her home at Jurong West Street 81.
